cusd_asset_id.descr: Asset ID of Confío Dollar token

cusd_circulating_supply.descr: Current circulating supply of collateral-backed cUSD

sponsor_address.descr: Sponsor address allowed to send app calls on behalf of users

tbills_backed_supply.descr: cUSD supply backed by T-bills/reserves (admin minted)

methods.name: create
methods.desc: Initialize the Confío Dollar contract

methods.name: set_sponsor_address
methods.desc:
Set the sponsor address that can send app calls on behalf of users
Admin only

methods.name: setup_assets
methods.desc:
Setup asset IDs and opt-in to both assets with proper funding
Must be called as part of atomic group with payment to app for fees/min balance
Group structure: - Tx 0: Payment to app (at least 0.6 ALGO for opt-ins and fees) - Tx 1: This app call

methods.name: pause
methods.desc: Pause all operations

methods.name: unpause
methods.desc: Unpause operations

methods.name: opt_in
methods.desc: Allow accounts to opt-in

methods.name: add_vault
methods.desc: Add a vault address

methods.name: remove_vault
methods.desc: Remove a vault address

methods.name: freeze_address
methods.desc: Freeze an address from transacting

methods.name: unfreeze_address
methods.desc: Unfreeze an address

methods.name: mint_admin
methods.desc:
Admin minting backed by T-bills or other reserves
This is separate from USDC collateralized minting Can be used for treasury-backed issuance

methods.name: burn_admin
methods.desc:
Admin burning to reduce supply (e.g., when selling T-bills)
Must be called with cUSD transfer to app

methods.name: mint_with_collateral
methods.desc:
Mint cUSD by depositing USDC (1:1 ratio)
Must be called as part of atomic group with USDC transfer
Supports two group structures:
Non-sponsored (2 transactions): - Tx 0: USDC transfer from user to app - Tx 1: This app call
Sponsored (3 transactions): - Tx 0: Payment from sponsor to user (or app) for fees - Tx 1: USDC transfer from user to app - Tx 2: This app call

methods.name: burn_for_collateral
methods.desc:
Burn cUSD to redeem USDC (1:1 ratio)
Must be called as part of atomic group with cUSD transfer
Supports two group structures:
Non-sponsored (2 transactions): - Tx 0: cUSD transfer from user to app - Tx 1: This app call
Sponsored (3 transactions): - Tx 0: Payment from sponsor to user (or app) for fees - Tx 1: cUSD transfer from user to app - Tx 2: This app call

methods.name: transfer_cusd
methods.desc:
Transfer Confío Dollar with freeze checks
Called alongside an ASA transfer transaction
Note: For stricter group binding, could require: - Global.group_size() == Int(2) - Txn.group_index() == Int(1) - asset_transfer matches Gtxn[0] Current implementation is sufficient since ASA freeze is enforced globally.

methods.name: update_admin
methods.desc:
Transfer admin rights to a new address (can be a multi-sig wallet)
Only current admin can transfer rights

methods.name: update_collateral_ratio
methods.desc:
Update collateral ratio (admin only)
1000000 = 1:1, 1500000 = 1.5:1 (150% collateralized) Range: 100%-200%

methods.name: refresh_reserve
methods.desc:
Refresh the stored reserve address from ASA parameters
Admin only - use if ASA reserve was intentionally rotated

methods.name: withdraw_usdc
methods.desc:
Withdraw USDC for treasury rebalancing (e.g., to purchase mTBILL)
Admin only - can be done while system is operational Maintains backing ratio by adjusting tracked reserves

methods.name: get_stats
methods.desc: Get minting and burning statistics

methods.name: get_reserves
methods.desc:
Get reserve statistics
Returns: (total_usdc_locked, cusd_circulating_supply, tbills_backed_supply, collateral_ratio, total_supply)

methods.name: verify_backing
methods.desc:
Verify that USDC reserves match or exceed cUSD supply
Returns (is_backed, actual_usdc_balance)

methods.name: is_frozen
methods.desc: Check if an address is frozen

methods.name: is_vault
methods.desc: Check if an address is a vault

methods.name: update
methods.desc: Only admin can update the application

methods.name: delete
methods.desc: Only admin can delete - require no outstanding supply and ASA reconfigured
